info.name: CatalogApi
info.description:
A collection of API methods for interacting with Gamma Powersports.

## Base URL

All request endpoints specified in this document are relative to the following base URL:

`https://api.gammapowersports.com`

request.description:
This endpoint accepts a shipToNumber and returns the matching shipping information from the Gamma System. If the list of available ship to numbers for your customer is unknown, you can use the Get Ship Tos request to get a complete list.

The response object contains the following fields:

- data - the result of the request. Contains the following fields:
    - shippingInformation - an object representing the shipping details for the given ship to number, containing the following fields:
        - shipToNo - the ship to number passed.
        - isDefault - true when ship to is the default ship to for your account in Gamma, false otherwise.  
            customerName - the account name for the ship to.
        - address - the address found on the ship to,
        - telephone - the phone number on the ship to.
        - city - the city for the ship to.
        - province - the standardized province code for the ship to.
        - postalCode - the postal code on the ship to.
        - country - the standardized country code for the ship to.
- error - an error block containing any errors. If the status is set to success it will be empty, otherwise it will contain the following fields:
    - code - the HTTP status code.
    - status - the HTTP status message.
    - message - a description of the error as well as any steps to be taken to correct the issue.
    - timestamp - the time at which the error occurred.
    - url - the URL at which the error occurred.
- status - the status of the request. Possible values are:
    - success - the request completed successfully and data should be available under the data field.
    - failed - the request failed due to an unexpected error. A generic error message will be available in the error field.
    - error - the request had an error which can be resolved by the user. A message field will be included in the error field with a description of the error and how it could be resolved.

response.name: Get Ship To - Success
Get Ship To - Error

request.description:
This endpoint will return a list of available ship to objects representing each ship to found for your dealer account.

The response will contain the following fields:

- data - the result of the request. Contains the following fields:
    - shippingInformation - a list of objects representing the shipping details for each ship to number found for your account. Each list object contains the following fields:
        - shipToNo - the ship to number passed.
        - isDefault - true when the ship to address is the default on your account, false otherwise.
        - customerName - the account name for the ship to.
        - address - the address found on the ship to.
        - telephone - the phone number on the ship to.
        - city - the city for the ship to.
        - province - the standardized province code on the ship to.
        - postalCode - the postal code on the ship to.
        - country - the standardized country code on the ship to.
- error - an error block containing any errors. Will always be empty if the status is set to success otherwise it will contain the following fields:
    - code - the HTTP status code.
    - status - the HTTP status message.
    - message - a description of the error as well as any steps to be taken to correct the issue.
    - timestamp - the time at which the error occurred.
    - url - the URL at which the error occurred.
- status - the status of the request. Possible values are:
    - success - the request completed successfully and data should be available under the data field.
    - failed - the request failed due to an unexpected error. A generic error message will be available in the error field.
    - error - the request had an error which can be resolved by the user. A message field will be included in the error field with a description of the error and how it could be resolved.

This endpoint accepts a part number and will return a JSON response containing stock level information. Optionally the item number can be included in the URL path rather than passed as a query string parameter. A request formatted this way would look like:

 `{{api_url}}/inventory/880-0004`.

response.name: Get Inventory Level - Success
Get Inventory Level - Item not Found

request.description:
This endpoint accepts a part number as a query string parameter and will return a JSON response containing item information. The fields returned are as follows:

- pricing - a block containing pricing information for the item based on the unit of measure of the product.
    - item - the item number associated to the pricing
    - price - the dealer specific price of the item
    - qty - the minimum quantity required for the price of this item
    - msrp - the manufacturer suggested retail price for the item
    - dealer - the dealer wholesale price for the item. Will match price field if no discount for the item is on file.
    - discount - the discount percentage received on the item
    - type - the type of discount received
- details - a block containing item information.
    - itemNumber - the item number matching the details
    - description1 - the main description for the item
    - description2 - secondary description information such as color, size, etc when applicable
    - imgRef - the web path to the item image. The path is not guaranteed and may result in a 404 when fetching. Due to this consider using a fallback image in the event of a missing image.
    - smallImgRef -The web path to the item thumbnail image. The path is not guaranteed and may result in a 404 when fetching. Due to this consider using a fallback image in the event of a missing image.
    - extendedDescription - HTML formatted description of product. Will not be present for all items.
    - techSpecs - HTML formatted block containing technical specifications for items. This may include sizing charts, fitment information, etc.
    - vendorPartNumber - the part number used by the vendor associated to the item
- inventory - this block contains the same information as the Inventory Check endpoint
    - quantity - the amount of stock available for the item. This will only show an exact value for quantities less than 99. Any quantity amount higher will show 99.
    - stockStatus - the status of the stock for the time. Can be 'In Stock' or 'Out of Stock'.

request.description:
This endpoint accepts a JSON payload containing order information. If the information is valid the order will be placed and a order number will be returned.
If the `testMode` option is passed with a `true` value, no order will be placed and only validation will occur. The order number returned when this is set to true will always be `-1-0`.

If the `shipToNumber` option is set to `99` (cross ship), the `shippingInformation` block with all of its options is required. If it is set to a valid `shipToNumber` in the Gamma System, (normal order) then the shipping information can be omitted and the ship to address on file will be used.
If the `allowBackorders` option is set to `true`, a stock check will not occur and any out of stock items will be shipped when they return to stock. However, if a discontinued item is requested with a greater stock than what is available, the order will not be placed and a message will be returned. Cross ship orders CANNOT be back ordered under any circumstances and will ignore this parameter.
The `shipMethod` parameter is optional. If it is passed it must match one of the options returned from the `Rate Shop Order` endpoint. If it is not passed, or if the passed value does not match one of the available ones, then the least expensive cost option will be selected.
The `customerPo` accepts a maximum of 20 characters.
A customer account number is not required in the request as the authorization token is linked to the dealer account.

response.name: Post Order - Cross Ship
Post Order - Non Cross Ship
Post Order - Cross Ship Missing Shipping

request.description:
This endpoint returns an estimate for an order request. It accepts the same payload as the Post Order method.

The response utilizes dealer specific discounts and applicable fees when determining the order estimate.

The freight cost and shipping method values represent the least expensive rate available.

The request returns all available freight methods with costs, in case an alternate carrier is preferred.

Similar to using the Post Order endpoint in test mode, order payload validation errors are returned.

The fields returned are as follows:

- data
    - message - Contains information regarding any system adjustments required for the order to validate. The only current condition is when the customer po value is too long - the system truncates to 20 characters.
    - order - the order estimate section
        - freightTotal - the portion of the grand total that represents the least expensive freight option.
        - grandTotal - the total cost of the order estimate
        - shipMethod - the default freight carrier used (least expensive)
        - taxTotal - the portion of the grand total that represents tax
        - rates - the list of available carriers and rates for the order
            - arrivalDate - estimated arrival date based on carrier provided
            - code - the carrier code which can be included in the Post Order request to select that carrier for the order.
            - description - the carrier service level description
        - shippingInformation - the shipping information for the order estimate.
            - shipToEmail
            - shipToName
            - streetAddress1
            - streetAddress2
            - telephone
            - city
            - province
            - postalCode
            - country
        - materialTotal - the portion of the grand total that represents the item cost
        - customerPo - the customer PO number for the original order. Will be truncated to 20 characters
        - items - the list of items on the order.
            - feeAmount - fee amounts for the item, such as environmental handling, etc., when applicable
            - feeDescription - the description for the item fee. Will be blank when no fees apply
            - quantity - the quantity ordered
            - extendedPrice - the price of the item, multiplied by the quantity.
            - price - the unit price of the item
            - description - the descriptive name of the item
            - extendedFeeAmount - the fee amount multiplied by the quantity.
            - partNumber - the Gamma part number for the item.
- error - a block containing error information if applicable.
    - code - the HTTP status code
    - status - the HTTP status description
    - message - the description of the error
    - timestamp - the UTC time the error
    - url - the endpoint web address of the error
    - invalidFields - the list of invalid fields on the original request.
        - field - the field identifier in the JSON payload
        - message - specific error message about the field.
- status - either success, error, or failed. Details about error or failed statuses can be found in the error block of the response.

Get Order Estimate

request.description:
This endpoint accepts an order number and returns a JSON block containing information for a matching order.

The order number can optionally include the BO number (three digit number prefixed with a dash (-)). If BO number is included a single order will be returned, otherwise, a list of orders will be returned. The second case may still result in only one order being returned, but the endpoint will respond with a list format. See the example reponses for more information.

The status field will be one of the following: - Received - the order has entered the Gamma system - Processing - the order is being processed by Gamma - Shipped - the order has been shipped by Gamma. If the status is set to Shipped then the order JSON will include a trackingInformation element containing the tracking number and carrier service description. Tracking information will be applied to the order as it is processed in the Gamma warehouse. If the tracking information is not being reported by the carrier, it will be registered once the package is scanned at the carrier depot. This usually happens later in the evening after Gamma pickup.

request.description:
This endpoint is used to get a paginated list of orders. It supports filtering, sorting, pages sizing, and pagination.

The request does not need any body by default. If no parameters are passed, a single page of 10 results is returned, sorted by descending order number. A default request with no parameters would be equal to passing the following request: { "max": 10, "page": 1, "filters": {}, "sort": { "sortBy": "ordernumber", "sortDirection": "desc" } } Filtering --------- The filters block supports the following fields: - idFrom - will return only results with an id equal or greater than this value. The value should not contain the bo number. Can be a numeric or string value. - idTo - will return only results with an id equal or less than this value. The value should not contain the the bo number. Can be a numeric or string value. - customerPo - will return results with a customer po containing this value. Case insensitive and should be passed as a string. - dateFrom - will return only results with a date equal or greater than this value. Should be in the format yyyyMMdd or yyyy-MM-dd and can be a numeric (if passed without -) or string value. - dateTo - will return only results with a date equal or less than this value. Should be in the format yyyyMMdd or yyyy-MM-dd and can be a numeric (if passed without -) or string value. - totalFrom - will return only results with an total equal or greater than this value. Can be a numeric or string value. - totalTo - will return only results with an total equal or less than this value. Can be a numeric or string value. - customerAddress - will return results with an address containing this value. Case insensitive and should be passed as a string value. - customerName - will return results with a customer name containing this value. Case insensitive and should be passed as a string value. - invoiceDateFrom - will return only results with an invoice date equal or greater than this value. Should be in the format yyyyMMdd or yyyy-MM-dd and can be a numeric (if passed without -) or string value. - invoiceDateTo - will return only results with an invoice date equal to or less than this value. Should be in the format yyyyMMdd or yyyy-MM-dd and can be a numeric (if passed without -) or string value. - orderType - will return orders matching this type. Defaults to `O`. Can be any of the following: - R - Returns (When this option is passed two new fields will appear in each order block, `originalOrderNumber` and `originalBoNumber`. These are the identifiers of the original order for which the return was created.) - O - Orders (default) - Q - Quotes - C - Credits - onlyDrop - will return only dropship results (ship-to of 99) if set to true. Can be any of the following: - true - false - 0 - 1 - onlyShipped - will return only shipped results (results with tracking information) if set to true. Can be any of the following: - true - false - 0 - 1 - onlyInvoiced - will return only invoiced orders. Can be used in conjunction with order type to find all processed returns. Can be any of the following: - true - false - 0 - 1 - status - will return only results matching one of the statuses found in this list. Available options are: - Received - Shipped - Processing Sorting ------- The sort block supports the following fields: - sortBy - the value to sort by. Supports the following options: - orderNumber - orderDate - orderTotal - customerName - customerAddress - sortDirection - the direction to sort by. Supports the following fields: - asc - desc Pagination ---------- Pagination can be controlled with the following two fields: - max - specifies the amount of results to be returned per page. - page - the page of results to return.

request.description:
This endpoint returns all distinct machine types. It supports filtering types by category and subcategory, which when passed, will only return types which contain fitments belonging to the given category/subcategory.

The endpoint accepts the following parameters:

*   category (optional) - the category label for returning machine types. When passed only types which have a fitment in the given category will be returned.
*   subCategory (optional) - the subcategory for returning machine types. When passed only types which have a fitment in the given subcategory will be returned.
*   ignoredCategories (optional) - a comma separated list of category labels to be omitted from the results.
*   itemList (optional)- a comma separated list of item numbers. If passed, only types which contain a fitment for one of the given items will be returned. Useful for creating a fitment selection for a single product or group of products.
    

The response object will contain the following fields:

*   data - the result of the request. Will contain the following fields:
    *   types - a list of machine makes which match the provided filters.
*   error - an error block containing any errors. Will always be empty if the `status` is set to `success` otherwise it will contain the following fields:
    *   error - the main error object containing the following fields:
        *   code - the HTTP status code.
        *   status - the HTTP status message.
        *   message - a description of the error as well as any steps to be taken to correct the issue.
        *   timestamp - the time at which the error occurred.
        *   url - the URL at which the error occurred.
*   status - the status of the request. Possible values are:
    *   success - the request completed successfully and data should be available under the `data` field.
    *   failed - the request failed due to an unexpected error. A generic error message will be available in the `error` field.
    *   error - the request had an error which can be resolved by the user. A message field will be included in the `error` field with a description of the error and how it could be resolved.

response.name: Get Type Options - Success

request.description:
This endpoint returns all distinct machine makes and accepts a mandatory type parameter as well as filter parameters. This endpoint can be used in conjunction with the 'Get Year Options' and 'Get Model Options' endpoints to create a Make-Year-Model selection application.

The endpoint accepts the following parameters:

*   type (optional) - the machine type for finding makes. Optional but recommended for machine filtering best results. Must match one of the options returned by the 'Get Type Options' request.
*   year (optional) - the machine year for finding makes. Allows for year as the first selection in a Year-Make-Model application configuration.
*   category (optional) - the category for returning machine makes. When passed, only the makes with a fitment in the given category will be returned.
*   subCategory (optional) - the subcategory for returning machine makes. When passed, only the makes having a fitment in the given subcategory will be returned.
*   ignoredCategories - a comma separated list of categories that will be omitted from the results.
*   itemList (optional)- a comma separated list of item numbers. If passed, only makes which contain a fitment for one of the given items will be returned. Useful for creating a fitment selection for a single product or group of products.
    

The response object will contain the following fields:

*   data - the result of the request. Will contain the following fields:
    *   makes- a list of machine makes which match the provided filters.
*   error - an error block containing any errors. Will always be empty if the `status` is set to `success` otherwise it will contain the following fields:
    *   error - the main error object containing the following fields:
        *   code - the HTTP status code.
        *   status - the HTTP status message.
        *   message - a description of the error as well as any steps to be taken to correct the issue.
        *   timestamp - the time at which the error occurred.
        *   url - the URL at which the error occurred.
*   status - the status of the request. Possible values are:
    *   success - the request completed successfully and data should be available under the `data` field.
    *   failed - the request failed due to an unexpected error. A generic error message will be available in the `error` field.
    *   error - the request had an error which can be resolved by the user. A message field will be included in the `error` field with a description of the error and how it could be resolved.

request.description:
This endpoint returns all distinct machine years and accepts a mandatory type parameter as well as filter parameters. This endpoint can be used in conjunction with the 'Get Make Options' and 'Get Model Options' endpoints to create a Make-Year-Model selection application.

The endpoint accepts the following parameters:

*   type (optional) - the machine type for finding years. Optional but recommended for machine filtering best results. Must match one of the options returned by the 'Get Type Options' request.
*   make (optional) - the machine make for finding years. Allows for selecting the make first in a Make-Year-Model application configuration.
*   category (optional) - the category for returning machine years. Only years having fitment in the given category will be returned.
*   subCategory (optional) - the subcategory for returning machine years. Only years having fitment in the given subcategory will be returned.
*   ignoredCategories - a comma separated list of categories which will be omitted from the results.
*   itemList (optional)- a comma separated list of item numbers. If passed, only years which contain a fitment for one of the given items will be returned. Useful for creating a fitment selection for a single product or group of products.
    

The response object will contain the following fields:

*   data - the result of the request. Will contain the following fields:
    *   years- a list of machine years which match the provided filters.
*   error - an error block containing any errors. Will always be empty if the `status` is set to `success` otherwise it will contain the following fields:
    *   error - the main error object containing the following fields:
        *   code - the HTTP status code.
        *   status - the HTTP status message.
        *   message - a description of the error as well as any steps to be taken to correct the issue.
        *   timestamp - the time at which the error occurred.
        *   url - the URL at which the error occurred.
*   status - the status of the request. Possible values are:
    *   success - the request completed successfully and data should be available under the `data` field.
    *   failed - the request failed due to an unexpected error. A generic error message will be available in the `error` field.
    *   error - the request had an error which can be resolved by the user. A message field will be included in the `error` field with a description of the error and how it could be resolved.

request.description:
This endpoint returns all distinct machine models and accepts mandatory type, make, and year parameters as well as filter parameters. This endpoint can be used in conjunction with the 'Get Make Options' and 'Get Year Options' endpoints to create a Make-Year-Model selection application.

The endpoint accepts the following parameters:

*   type (optional) - the machine type for finding models. Optional but recommended for machine filtering best results. Must match one of the options returned by the 'Get Type Options' request.
*   make - the machine make for finding models.
*   year - the machine year for finding models.
*   category (optional) - the category for returning machine models. When passed, only models having fitment in the given category will be returned.
*   subCategory (optional) - the subcategory for returning machine models. When passed only models having fitment in the given subcategory will be returned.
*   ignoredCategories (optional) - a comma separated list of categories to be omitted from the results.
*   itemList (optional)- a comma separated list of item numbers. If passed, only models which contain a fitment for one of the given items will be returned. Useful for creating a fitment selection for a single product or group of products.
    

The response object will contain the following fields:

*   data - the result of the request. Will contain the following fields:
    *   models- a list of machine makes which match the provided filters.
*   error - an error block containing any errors. Will always be empty if the `status` is set to `success` otherwise it will contain the following fields:
    *   error - the main error object containing the following fields:
        *   code - the HTTP status code.
        *   status - the HTTP status message.

The endpoint accepts a make, year, and model as well as optional category, subcategory, and ignoredCategories filters and will return all fitment products which match. Parameters are as follows:

*   make - the make of the fitment records to find. Must match one of the options returned by the 'Get Fitment Models' request.
*   year - the year of the fitment records to find. Must match one of the options returned by the 'Get Fitment Models' request.
*   model - the model of the fitment records to find. Must match one of the options returned by the 'Get Fitment Models' request.
*   category (optional) - a product category results filter. If passed, only fitments which match this category will be returned. Must match one of the options returned from the 'Get Fitment Categories' request.
*   subCategory (optional) - a product subcategory results filter. If passed, only fitments which match this subcategory will be returned. Must match one of the options returned from the 'Get Fitment Categories' request.
*   onlyInStock (optional) - if value passed equals true, only fitments for in stock items will be returned.
*   ignoredCategories (optional)- a comma separated list of categories to omit from the results. If passed, no records will be returned with this category. Must match one of the values returned by the 'Get Fitment Categories' request.
*   itemList (optional)- a comma separated list of item numbers. If passed, only products matching an item number found in this list will be returned. Useful for creating a fitment selection for a single product or group of products.

*   data - the result of the request. Will contain the following fields:

request.description:
This endpoint is used to return categories and subcategories related to products requiring fitment. The endpoint supports filtering options to target specific categories. When parameters are included, set the `ignoreCache` parameter equal to true, or all categories will be returned. The endpoint supports the following parameters:

*   type (optional) - the machine type for categories to be returned. Supported options are returned in the Get Type Options method. Current supported options (may be subject to change) include:
    *   ATV
    *   UTV/SXS
    *   OFF-ROAD MOTORCYCLE
    *   STREET MOTORCYCLE
    *   SNOWMOBILE
    *   SCOOTER
    *   PWC
*   make (optional) - the machine make related to categories being requested. Can be used in conjunction with `year` and `model` filters to find available categories for specific machine.
*   year (optional) - the machine year relating to requested categories. Can be used in conjunction with `make` and `model` filters to find available categories for a specific machine.
*   model (optional) - the machine model relating to requested categories. Can be used in conjunction with `year` and `make` filters to find available categories for a specific machine.
*   category (optional) - the specific category to return. Can be used to determine all subcategories for a specific category.
*   ignoreCache (optional) - the full response (no filters) is cached to improve performance. If any filters are used this parameter should be set to true in the response, or else the cached full category response will be returned.
*   ignoredCategories (optional) - a comma separated list of categories which will be excluded from the response.
    

The response will contain the following fields:

*   data - the result of the request. Will contain the following fields:
    *   fitmentCategories - a list of objects, each representing a fitment categories. Each list object will contain the following fields:
        *   type - the machine type for the category.
        *   category - the main category.
        *   subCategory - the sub category which can be grouped by the `category` field.
*   error - an error block containing any errors. Will always be empty if the `status` is set to `success` otherwise it will contain the following fields:

request.description:
This endpoint is used to find fitments for similar machines within a given type and category. Since multiple model formats can exist for a single machine, this method returns a wider range fitment products for fitment verification. Machines in the same categories, make, year and (optionally) engine size are returned . The parameters for this endpoint are:

*   type - the product type of the machine. Must match one of the values returned in the 'Get Fitment Categories' request.
*   category- the category of fitments to include in the response. Must match one of the values returned in the 'Get Fitment Categories' request.
*   make - the make of the machine. Must match one of the values returned by the 'Get Fitment Models' request.
*   year - the year of the machine to find similar models for. Must match one of the values returned by the 'Get Fitment Models' request.
*   model (optional)- the model of the machine. Must match one of the values returned by the 'Get Fitment Models' request. Must be included when `filterEngineSize` parameter is set to true or all engine sizes will still be returned.
*   subCategory (optional)- the subcategory of fitments to include in the results. Must match one of the values returned by the 'Get Fitment Models' request.
*   filterEngineSize (optional)- if true, only similar models with the same engine size of the original machine will be returned. If false, any fitments with the same originating make and year will be returned regardless of engine size. Will deliver more specific and smaller result set if sent as true.
*   itemList (optional)- a comma separated list of item numbers. If passed, type and category can be omitted and fitments/descriptions will only be returned which match one of the provided item numbers.
    

The response object will contain the following fields:

*   data - the result of the request. Will contain the following fields:
    *   fitments - a list of fitments for similar machines. Each element in this list will contain:
        *   notes - an object containing the notes for each SKU. Values will depend on what SKUs are available, not all SKUs will have notes. See example response.
        *   engineSize - the engine size for the machine represented by this element.
        *   make - the fitment make for the machine represented by this element.
        *   years - the fitment years for the machine represented by this element.
        *   model - the fitment model for the machine represented by this element.
        *   This element can additionally contain any number of keys matching the values found in the `descriptions` field below.
    *   descriptions - a list of descriptions in each fitment element found in the `fitments` field outlined above. There is no guarantee that a description found in this list will exist in all fitment elements, but each will be found in at least one fitment element.
*   error - an error block containing any errors. Will always be empty if the `status` is set to `success` otherwise it will contain the following fields:
    *   error - the main error object containing the following fields:
        *   code - the HTTP status code.
        *   status - the HTTP status message.
        *   message - a description of the error as well as any steps to be taken to correct the issue.
        *   timestamp - the time at which the error occurred.
        *   url - the URL at which the error occurred.
*   status - the status of the request. Possible values are:
    *   success - the request completed successfully and data should be available under the `data` field.
    *   failed - the request failed due to an unexpected error. A generic error message will be available in the `error` field.
